<br>
Marriage does not automatically turn you into someone else, totally dependant on another person. I am married and I am the same person with the same interests as when I was single (except scoutin for guys). The only difference is I <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>choose</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> to stay home with my child now and I choose to share my life with someone I love dearly. Until I stayed home I made my own money paid my own bills and had my own bank account. We just paid some bills together.<br>
<br>
Marriage from any stand point is not an evil thing. I just think <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>everyone</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> who wants to get married legally should be able to. Even ,like someone said, if three people want to get married it is their business. Our government is supposed to represent all of our interests, not dictate them. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.comcast.net/~dremarian/wsb/media/68398/site1026.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
<!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=440005" target="top"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:maroon;font-family:georgia;font-size:x-small;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Graph's toys</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ammelen>Ammelen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I Live Here</span><br>  Posts: 1371<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/9/03 1:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=122.topic&index=47>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Abolish Marriage</span><hr size=1> Any way you look at it, marriage is a loss of independence.  You owe the person you marry your time.  I prefer to use my time as I please doing whatever interests me.  I prefer not to be attached to one particular person.  I don't want the obligations of children at this point in my life.<br>
<br>
I don't want to ever take the risk of having to pay money (alimony) to someone I don't like.  I won't give the court the opportunity to make me do that.<br>
<br>
Marriage isn't necessarily a bad thing, it depends on the person.  I am only suggesting that it would be a bad thing for me, as I consider what I would lose to be of greater value than what I would gain.  For some people, the inequality would be reversed.<br>
<br>
I don't care if 3 people want to marry or not either.  However, if the government got out of the whole marriage business, it wouldn't have legal ramifications, and this type of thing would be fine.  As long as the marriage contract works as it does now, there are huge legal ramifications that make the whole thing into a big mess.  Take the government out of marriage, make it a non-legal personal decision, and the government won't have to care.<br>
<br>
Ammelen <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=misscheivous>MissCheivous</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>New User</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/9/03 9:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=122.topic&index=48>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Abolish Marriage</span><hr size=1> I see your point Ammelen. It is not the right thing for you. But hopefully someday if you do get married the last thing on your mind will be divorce. And if you truely love the person (the good and bad) then you would gain infinite amounts more than you would lose. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
My parents met on a blind date, six weeks later they got married and 35 years later they are still together and in love. I just want people to know sometimes marriages do work. I'm not saying they are cake. Because it is hard work, but worth it.<br>
<br>
I think part of the reason the divorce rate is so high is because some people have an unrealistic expectation of marriage, like it is somehow going fix their relationship or make things better. The person you choose to marry will be the same person you dated and/or lived with. People don't change very often so choose wisely. And please don't run yourself into the poorhouse having the wedding of your dreams. Is it really worth the years of fighting over the bills for one day? We spent about 200 $ on the rings and the magistrate and believe me we were better off. Look at it as the money you go into debt for for your wedding is taking away from the house of your dreams. In which hopfully you'll spend many many wonderful years together. Unless you're rich then go for it. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  I know this is a bit off topic, but I just wanted to throw it in there. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.comcast.net/~dremarian/wsb/media/68398/site1026.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
